sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36778
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: DNA damage sensor with Gemini Reporter (weak LexA Generator)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Attaches BBa_M36777 to a Gemini actuator so it can report out.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Evan Clark

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36777
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: DNA damage sensor with weak LexA generator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Same as our BBa_M36053 DNA damage sensor, but using a weaker 5' UTR in the LexA generator so not as much LexA is generated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Evan Clark
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: LexA gene and promoter from E. coli genome, other parts from registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This sensor with a weaker LexA generator is another candidate for level matching with the Gemini actuator we will attach to the damage sensor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36709
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A medium strength RBS expressing Gemini, ending with a strong terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeff Quinn and Wyatt Woodson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Gemini, a Bifunctional Enzymatic and Fluorescent Reporter of Gene Expression. PLOS One. Lance Martin et al.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_E0051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a fusion protein between GFP and the alpha fragment of lacZ. It can be measured via fluorescence from GFP or through an assay for beta-galactosidase in a strain containing the omega fragment of lacZ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Austin Che
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: amino acids 3-60 from lacZ and amino acids 2-end of GFP (E0043)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The amino acid linker AGGSEGGGSEHHHHHHGSE is between the lacZa and GFP. The 6-his can also facilitate detection on a Western blot, for purification, etc.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter sequence for the LexA gene. The lexA protein regulates its own promoter. There is a common binding site for the lexA protein found in this promoter that is also found in ~40 other SOS genes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Kent
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We know exactly were the lexA protein binds, but we are not entirely sure of the exact deliniation of the promoter itself. Therefore this sequence may contain superfluous information.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: E. coli RNA pol transcription terminator designed and tested by Guillaume Cambray at BIOFAB Emeryville. Based on the natural E. coli rnpB T1 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Guillaume Cambray et al. c/o BIOFAB Emeryville

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36050
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LexA is a repressor that represses SOS response genes coding for DNA polymerases required for repairing DNA damage.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ryan Kent, Evan Clark

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 5' Bicistronic UTR (weak), does not include ATG start
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: 5' UTR based on bicistronic junction architecture. First RBS is strong and drives expression of short leader cistron. Second RBS internal to first cistron control translation of gene of interest. Architecture is optimized so that downstream CDS for gene of interest does not have a chance to form a secondary structure with the 5' UTR. See BIOFAB.org for more information.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: c/o Vivek Mutalik et al. BIOFAB Emeryville
